          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-01-21 07:03:29.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 osd: cache LOVEA in osd-ldiskfs",
        "message": "LU-0000 osd: cache LOVEA in osd-ldiskfs\n\nthere is an idea that EA fetching is an expensive operation which\naffects creation rate. it's interesting to know whether we could\nmove LOV EA caching down to OSD and solve the outstanding with\ncaching LOV EA in LOD which is hard to revalidate when an object\nis being accessed via OUT.\n\nthe primary purpose of the patch is to verify the approch is\nfunctionally correct. then we'll be able to benchmark it.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ie7925c94cc2147c3650af18c6118523d48624ebe\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
